ns kingin LA, despite growing public transit options.\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thecar\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 329}, {\"ngram\": \"kingin LA\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"growing public transit options\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When LA hosted the Games in 1932, it hadan extensive public transportation system, with buses and anextensive network of electric streetcars.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 414}, {\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"anextensive network\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"electric streetcars\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, the trolleys are long gone; riders say city busesdon't come on schedule, and bus stops are dirty.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trolleys\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 573}, {\"ngram\": \"city busesdon't\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"schedule\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"bus stops\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What happened?\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This question fascinates me because I am abusiness professorwho studies why society abandons and then sometimes returns to certain technologies, such asvinyl records,landline phones, andmetal coins.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This question\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"abusiness professorwho studies\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"certain technologies\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"such asvinyl records\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"phones\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"andmetal coins\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The demise of electric streetcars in Los Angeles and attempts to bring them back today vividly demonstrate the costs and challenges of such revivals.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The demise\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"electric streetcars\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"the costs\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"challenges\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"such revivals\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2028 Olympic Games will be held in existing sports venues around Los Angeles and are expected to host 15,000 athletes and over 1 million spectators.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2028 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"existing sports venues\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"15,000 athletes\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1 million spectators\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transportation is a critical priority in any city, but especially so in Los Angeles, which has been a sprawling metropolis from the start.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transportation\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"a critical priority\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"any city\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprawling metropolis\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early 1900s, railroad magnateHenry Huntington, who owned vast tracts of land around LA, started subdividing his holdings into small plots and building homes.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington,_West_Virginia\", \"score\": 0.7334748790710081, \"rank\": 0.2644960314869742, \"text\": \"Huntington\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington,_West_Virginia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huntington,_West_Virginia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the early 1900s\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"vast tracts\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"land\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"his holdings\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"small plots\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1441}, {\"ngram\": \"building homes\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to attract buyers, he alsobuilt a trolley systemthat whisked residents from outlying areas to jobs and shopping downtown.\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1470}, {\"ngram\": \"buyers\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"a trolley\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"systemthat\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"outlying areas\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"shopping downtown\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the 1930s, Los Angeles had a vibrant public transportation network, with over 1,000 miles of electric streetcar routes, operated by two companies:Pacific Electric Railway, with its \\\"Red Cars,\\\" andLos Angeles Railway, with its \\\"Yellow Cars.\\\"\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Electric\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pacific Electric Railway\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Electric\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Electric\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1930s\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"a vibrant public transportation network\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1,000 miles\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"electric streetcar routes\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"two companies\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"Red Cars\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"andLos Angeles Railway\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"Yellow Cars\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The system wasn't perfect by any means.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1878, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The system\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"any means\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many people felt that streetcars were inconvenient and also unhealthy when they were jammed with riders.\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many people\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"streetcars\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, streetcars were slow because they had to share the road with automobiles.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"streetcars\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2049}, {\"ngram\": \"automobiles\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As auto usage climbed and roads became congested, travel times increased.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"auto usage\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"roads\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2099}, {\"ngram\": \"travel times\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless, many Angelenos rode the streetcars-especially during World War II, when gasoline was rationed and automobile plants shifted to producing military vehicles.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many Angelenos\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"the streetcars\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"World War II\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"gasoline\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"automobile plants\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"military vehicles\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1910, Los Angeles had a widely used local rail network, with over 1,200 miles (1,930 kilometers) of track.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a widely used local rail network\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1,200 miles\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"1,930 kilometers\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What happened?\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2437, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The end of the war marked theend of the line for streetcars.\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The end\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2457}, {\"ngram\": \"marked theend\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2471}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"streetcars\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The war effort had transformed oil, tire, and car companies into behemoths, and these industriesneeded new buyersfor goods from the massive factories they had built for military production.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The war effort\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"oil\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"tire\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"car companies\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"behemoths\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2574}, {\"ngram\": \"goods\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2622}, {\"ngram\": \"the massive factories\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"military production\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Civilians and returning soldiers were tired of rationing and war privations, and they wanted to spend money on goods such as cars.\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Civilians\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"soldiers\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"rationing and war privations\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2765}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"goods\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2806}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afteryears of heavy usageduring the war, Los Angeles' streetcar system needed an expensive capital upgrade.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2863, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Afteryears\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2832}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy usageduring\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2853}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"an expensive capital upgrade\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in the mid-1940s, most of the system was sold to a company called National City Lines, which waspartly owned by the carmaker General Motors, the oil companies Standard Oil of California and Phillips Petroleum, and the Firestone tire company.\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 3175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3000, \"end\": 3019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_City_Lines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National City Lines\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_City_Lines\", \"dbpedia\