to\": 3544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some researchers argue that the systemwould have died on its own, like manyother streetcar networks around the world.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3663, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some researchers\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3562}, {\"ngram\": \"the systemwould\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3589}, {\"ngram\": \"manyother streetcar networks\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3645}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3653, \"to\": 3662}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversy evenspilled over into pop culturein the 1988 movieWho Framed Roger Rabbit, which came down firmly on the conspiracy side.\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The controversy\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3680}, {\"ngram\": \"pop culturein\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1988 movieWho Framed Roger Rabbit\", \"from\": 3717, \"to\": 3754}, {\"ngram\": \"the conspiracy side\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What's undisputed is that, starting in the mid-1940s, powerful social forces transformed Los Angeles so that commuters had only two choices: drive or take a public bus.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3893, \"end\": 3904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mid-1940s\", \"from\": 3843, \"to\": 3856}, {\"ngram\": \"powerful social forces\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"commuters\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"only two choices\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3943}, {\"ngram\": \"a public bus\", \"from\": 3959, \"to\": 3971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, LA became so choked with traffic that it often took hours to cross the city.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4062, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 3976, \"to\": 3984}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 3986, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic\", \"from\": 4011, \"to\": 4018}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4043}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1990, the Los Angeles Times reported that people wereputting refrigerators, desks, and televisions in their carsto cope with getting stuck in horrendous traffic.\", \"from\": 4064, \"to\": 4228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4077, \"end\": 4094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.364362785730378e-37, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4115}, {\"ngram\": \"refrigerators\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4141}, {\"ngram\": \"desks\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4148}, {\"ngram\": \"televisions\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4165}, {\"ngram\": \"horrendous traffic\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A swath of movies, fromFalling DowntoCluelesstoLa La Land, have featured the next-level challenge of driving in LA.\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4344, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A swath\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4236}, {\"ngram\": \"movies\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4246}, {\"ngram\": \"the next-level challenge\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4326}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 4341, \"to\": 4343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traffic was also a concern when LA hosted the 1984 Summer Games, but theGames went off smoothly.\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Traffic\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4353}, {\"ngram\": \"a concern\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4372}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4380}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1984 Summer Games\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4409}, {\"ngram\": \"theGames\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers convinced over 1 million people to ride buses, and theygot many trucks to drive during off-peakhours.\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4453}, {\"ngram\": \"over 1 million people\", \"from\": 4464, \"to\": 4485}, {\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 4494, \"to\": 4499}, {\"ngram\": \"many trucks\", \"from\": 4513, \"to\": 4524}, {\"ngram\": \"off-peakhours\", \"from\": 4541, \"to\": 4554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2028 games, however,will have roughly 50 percent moreathletes competing, which means thousands more coaches, family, friends, and spectators.\", \"from\": 4556, \"to\": 4701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2028 games\", \"from\": 4556, \"to\": 4570}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly 50 percent\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4608}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands more coaches\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4667}, {\"ngram\": \"family\", \"from\": 4669, \"to\": 4675}, {\"ngram\": \"friends\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4684}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So simply dusting off plans from 40 years ago will not work.\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4729}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, Los Angeles is slowly rebuilding a more robust public transportation system.\", \"from\": 4764, \"to\": 4847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4771, \"end\": 4782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more robust public transportation system\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to buses, it now hasfour light-rail lines-the new name for electric streetcars-and two subways.\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 4955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4859}, {\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4868}, {\"ngram\": \"hasfour light-rail lines\", \"from\": 4877, \"to\": 4901}, {\"ngram\": \"the new name\", \"from\": 4902, \"to\": 4914}, {\"ngram\": \"electric streetcars\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 4938}, {\"ngram\": \"two subways\", \"from\": 4943, \"to\": 4954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many followthe same routes that electric trolleys once traveled.\", \"from\": 4956, \"to\": 5020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many followthe same routes\", \"from\": 4956, \"to\": 4982}, {\"ngram\": \"electric trolleys\", \"from\": 4988, \"to\": 5005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rebuilding this network iscosting the public billions, since the old system was completely dismantled.\", \"from\": 5021, \"to\": 5123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this network\", \"from\": 5032, \"to\": 5044}, {\"ngram\": \"the public billions\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5074}, {\"ngram\": \"the old system\", \"from\": 5082, \"to\": 5096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three key improvements are planned for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5125, \"to\": 5177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Three key improvements\", \"from\": 5125, \"to\": 5147}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5164, \"to\": 5176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, LA's airport terminals will beconnected to the rail system.\", \"from\": 5178, \"to\": 5244, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LA's airport terminals\", \"from\": 5185, \"to\": 5207}, {\"ngram\": \"the rail system\", \"from\": 5228, \"to\": 5243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, the Los Angeles organizing committee is planning heavily on using buses to move people.\", \"from\": 5245, \"to\": 5340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5257, \"end\": 5268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9992495165633384, \"rank\": 0.0007509828495883192, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5324}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 5333, \"to\": 5339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will do this by reassigning some lanes away from cars andmaking them available for 3,000 more buses, which will be borrowed from other locales.\", \"from\": 5341, \"to\": 5487, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some lanes\", \"from\": 5372, \"to\": 5382}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 5393, \"to\": 5397}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000 more buses\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5443}, {\"ngram\": \"other locales\", \"from\": 5473, \"to\": 5486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, there are plans to permanently increase bicycle lanes around the city.\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5568, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"plans\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5513}, {\"ngram\": \"bicycle lanes\", \"from\": 5538, \"to\": 5551}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5559, \"to\": 5567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, one major initiative,a bike path along the Los Angeles River, is still under an environmental review that may not be completed by 2028.\", \"from\": 5569, \"to\": 5713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5621, \"end\": 5638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles River\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_River\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one major initiative\", \"from\": 5578, \"to\": 5598}, {\"ngram\": \"a bike path\", \"from\": 5599, \"to\": 5610}, {\"ngram\": \"an environmental review\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I expect thatorganizers will pull off a car-free Olympics, simply by making driving and parking conditions so awful during the Games that people are forced to take public transportation to sports venues around the city.\", \"from\": 5715, \"to\": 5934, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thatorganizers\", \"from\": 5724, \"to\": 5738}, {\"ngram\": \"a car-free Olympics\", \"from\": 5753, \"to\": 5772}, {\"ngram\": \"driving\", \"from\": 5791, \"to\": 5798}, {\"ngram\": \"parking conditions\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5821}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5838, \"to\": 5847}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 5859}, {\"ngram\": \"public transportation\", \"from\": 5879, \"to\": 5900}, {\"ngram\": \"sports venues\", \"from\": 5904, \"to\": 5917}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 5925, \"to\": 5933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Games end, however, most of LA is likely to quickly revert to its car-centric ways.\", \"from\": 5935, \"to\": 6028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games end\", \"from\": 5941, \"to\": 5954}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 5973, \"to\": 5975}, {\"ngram\": \"its car-centric ways\", \"from\": 6007, \"to\": 6027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AsCasey Wasserman, chair of theLA 2028organizing committee, recently put it: \\\"The unique thing about Olympic Games is for 17 days you can fix a lot of problems when you can set the rules-for traffic, for fans, for commerce-than you do on a normal day in Los Angeles.\\\"\", \"from\": 6030, \"to\": 6297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6038, \"end\": 6047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lew_Wasserman\", \"score\": 0.9999998295925397, \"rank\": 1.7040762926657435e-07, \"text\": \"Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lew_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia